@startuml component-architecture
!include plantuml-dark.inc.puml
title Ski Resort Conditions Dashboard — cloud and application components

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

package "End user" {
  [Angular SPA\n(ski-resort-dashboard)] as SPA <<browser>>
}

cloud "AWS" {
  together {
    [Amazon CloudFront] as CF
    [Amazon S3\n(static hosting)] as S3
  }

  [API Gateway\n(HTTP API)] as APIGW
  [Application Load Balancer] as ALB

  frame "Amazon ECS\n(Fargate)" as ECS {
    [SkiResort.Api\n.NET 8 container] as API <<container>>
    [AWS Distro for OpenTelemetry\n(ADOT collector sidecar)] as ADOT <<container>>
  }

  database "Amazon RDS\nPostgreSQL" as RDS
  database "Amazon DynamoDB\nSkiResortUserFavorites" as DDB
  queue "Amazon SQS\nweather ingestion" as SQS
  [Amazon CloudWatch\n(logs / metrics / traces)] as CW
}

SPA --> CF : HTTPS\n(SPA assets)
CF --> S3 : origin (OAC)

SPA --> APIGW : HTTPS\n/api/* and negotiate
APIGW --> ALB : proxy integration
ALB --> API : HTTP :8080

API --> RDS : EF Core, Dapper
API --> DDB : favorites (IAmazonDynamoDB)
API --> SQS : receive / delete messages
API --> ADOT : OTLP gRPC\n(127.0.0.1:4317)
ADOT --> CW : export telemetry

SPA ..> API : SignalR\n/hubs/resort-conditions\n(same API origin or gateway)

note right of API
  REST controllers (resorts, reports,
  favorites, settings), SignalR hub,
  SqsIngestionWorker, WeatherSyncWorker,
  session middleware, OpenTelemetry SDK
end note

@enduml
